snippet.title: The Nature in Japan 4K / Kiso - Nagano
snippet.description:
Kiso is an area abundant in nature located in Nagano Prefecture, Japan. 
It is situated in a valley at the foot of Mt. Ontake, through which the Kiso River flows. 
As the seasons change from winter to spring, the snow melts, and the area benefits from rich meltwater flowing down from the mountains.
In spring, many beautiful cherry blossoms then bloom.

All footages used in this video is original footage we shot.

PRIMAL EARTH

snippet.title: Northern Mariana Islands -The Paradise of Amazing Views 4K
snippet.description:
The Northern Mariana Islands are a paradise of amazing views.
There are endless crystal clear ocean, a land teeming with life and star-filled skies.
The islands of Saipan, Tinian, and Rota.
These small islands offer spectacular scenery as far as the eyes can see.

The Northern Mariana Islands are an archipelago in northwestern Micronesia. 
It borders the Northwestern Pacific Ocean to the east and the Philippine Sea to the west.

All footages used in this video is original footage we shot.
